longBusinessSummary: IEI Integration Corp. provides industrial computer products worldwide. It provides AIoT and edge computing products, DevCloud solutions, PUZZLE Dev. Kits, FLEX AIoT developer kits, TANK AIoT developer kits, AIoT edge insights solutions, embedded systems, AI training server systems, VPU, FPGA, and CPU accelerators, backplanes, and assistant robots; networking products comprising network appliances, including routers, VPN, switches, firewalls, UTMs, etc.; and storage servers, network modules, and industrial network switches. The company also offers embedded computers consisting of full size and half size single board computers; industrial motherboards and embedded boards; ETX/COM EXPRESS/Q7; PEMUX series backplanes; rackmount, embedded, and compact chassis; LCD converter boards; PCI/PCIe expansion cards; and wireless, mini-PCIe, and TPM modules. In addition, it provides embedded systems, including AI-powered box PCs, DIN-rail embedded systems, rugged box PCs, compact size embedded systems, medical box PCs, transportation embedded systems, digital signage embedded systems, and QTS gateways, as well as rackmount, embedded, and compact chassis; panel PC and monitor products, such as heavy and light industrial, RISC-based, healthcare, and transportation PCs; industrial monitors; and handheld devices. Further, the company offers power supply products, adapters, DC UPS modules, DC to DC modules, and peripherals, such as industrial compact flash cards, CPU coolers, cables and connectors, mounting kits and stands, drive bays, and e-window tool kits. Its products are used in computer-based applications, such as factory automation, computer telephony integration, networking appliances, security, and systems, as well as in various fields comprising the Internet of Things, national defense, police administration, transportation, communication base stations, and medical instruments. IEI Integration Corp. was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in New Taipei City, Taiwan.
